---
export const prerender = true;

import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---
<Layout title="Home">
    <h1><span class="title-wildcard">*.&nbsp;</span>is-in.nz</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      A quiet corner of the web: one hostname with a profile, short links you can
      repoint, and mail forwarded to where you already read it—without the noise
      of generic hosting or another social graph.
    </p>
    <p>
      You keep the decisions that matter: where your links land, how your page
      reads, who receives mail for your name. The rest stays small and out of the
      way.
    </p>
    <p>
      Underneath, the bet is on simple, reliable technology—affordable to run,
      dependable by design, and meant to be supported for decades, not months.
    </p>
    <hr>
    <footer>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/claim">Reserve a subdomain</a></li>
      </ul>
    </footer>
</Layout>
